---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 92
  - Title: Srimad Bhagavatam
    Location: XI xiv
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Hold of Passion
---
By attributing worth to tangible objects, man becomes attracted to them;
attraction to them brings desire for them; desire leads to competition and
dispute amongst men. These rouse violent anger, and the result is delusion.
Delusion completely overcomes man's sense of right and wrong.
